headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 31 points and finally got a couple of shots to drop from long range to help the Orlando Magic beat the Charlotte Hornets 117-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 31 points, Magic beat Hornets 117-106

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray's career high in scoring helped give Quin Snyder his first win with the Atlanta Hawks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray's 39 help Hawks beat Blazers for Snyder's first win

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges was considered a defensive star and complementary offensive player in Phoenix before abruptly having his five-year run there ended when he was shipped to Brooklyn as part of the trade that sent Kevin Durant to the Suns.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mikal Bridges helps Nets rally to stun Celtics, 115-105

events.name: New York Knicks at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Here's just some of the things Julius Randle did in the final seconds Friday night: He lost the ball, fell to the floor, sent New York coach Tom Thibodeau sprawling and...
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 43, Knicks win 8th straight, top Heat 122-120

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant sees a loaded roster and all the possibilities that come with it for the Phoenix Suns.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Durant, Okogie lead Suns to 125-104 romp over Bulls

events.name: Utah Jazz at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Aaron Wiggins scored 27 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Utah Jazz 130-103 on Friday night to snap a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins scores 27 as Thunder top Jazz to end 5-game skid

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 18 points, 18 rebounds and 10 assists for his 25th triple-double this season to lead the Denver Nuggets over the Memphis Grizzlies 113-97 Friday night in a showdown of the top two teams in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's triple-double lifts Nuggets over Grizzlies 113-97

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 27 points and hit the go-ahead 3-pointer, helping the Golden State Warriors wrap up a perfect homestand with a 108-99 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 27 points, Warriors beat Pelicans 108-99

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis made two free throws with seven seconds left to cap a near-triple double in the Sacramento Kings' 128-127 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis hits winning free throw, Kings beat Clippers 128-127

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 22 points and 14 rebounds, Anthony Edwards scored 19 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves completed a two-game Los Angeles sweep with a 110-102 victory over the short-handed Lakers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert leads Timberwolves past Lakers despite Davis' 38
